org.kepler.provenance.sql

Class SQLRecordingV8

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kepler.provenance.Recording
      • org.kepler.provenance.sql.SQLRecording
        • org.kepler.provenance.sql.SQLRecordingV7
          • org.kepler.provenance.sql.SQLRecordingV8

  • public class SQLRecordingV8
extends SQLRecordingV7
    SQL provenance output. NOTE: The v8 schema is under development and likely to change. This uses version 8 of the schema. New features:
    • Saving the workflow contents for each execution.
    • Saving contents of files referenced in tokens.
    • Each workflow and workflow execution has unique LSID.
    • Workflow name no longer required.
    • Explicit mapping from token write to token read.
    • Combining actor firing events into a single "firing cycle event".
    • Recording execution exceptions.
    • Storing associated data for executions.
    Author:
    Derik Barseghian, Daniel Crawl, Ben Leinfelder, Sean Riddle
